Hi,

TS Version: 1.0.1
VS Version: 2013 Update 2

Here is the repro:

```TypeScript
// Step 1
function foo(bar: string) { }

// Step 2
foo('');

// Step 3
foo('dd'); // So far so good

// Step 4
foo('dd,'); // Completion springs up
```

The expected behaviour is for the completion list to not appear when the comma is typed inside the string literal.

The same behaviour occurs when an opening parenthesis "(" is typed within the string.
